<blockquote>
<p>10:11:29 &lt;AidenEldritch&gt; it's like the SCP equivalent of edging<br />
10:11:36 &lt;AidenEldritch&gt; not everyone will be enthused by it</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It took me a moment of frustration, but I get now why you went with the hype train approach. Audience retention on such a massive project is going to be a tough one, especially with your drier style. Releasing your pieces over time helps build on that rising tension that's been present in all the skips leading to this, and gives people the opportunity to read two or three articles at a time instead of having to commit to whatever ridiculous soup of skips and tales is in the final project - that's going to be a big issue for people arriving after the 11th, but whatever.</p>
<p>Novoting until it's complete, but I like where this is going. There's an enormous amount of work behind this.</p>

